text: Bouchra Fatima Zohra Hirech (born 22 August 2000) is an Algerian weightlifter. == Career == Hirech studied at the Mostaganem School. Aged 15, she won a bronze medal in the 75 kg division at the 2016 African Weightlifting Championships. At the 2016 Olympics she competed in the +75 kg category and placed last. ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Olympic weightlifters of Algeria Category:Weightlifters at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Algerian female weightlifters Category:Competitors at the 2019 African Games Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:African Games competitors for Algeria
